markets.title: Will  above 25 or above Starship launches reach space in 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If above 24 Starship launches reach Space in 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: A Starship will be considered to have reached space if its maximum altitude is at least 62 miles above sea level at any point during its flight. Each launch is considered separate and will contribute to  <count> separately, even if the same Starship is launched multiple times. (For example, if in <period> the same Starship is launched twice and reaches space twice, <count> will be 2).
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.
